        <div class="panel-heading panel-custom-green">
          Booking Information
        </div>
        <div class="panel-body">
          <p>Iberia, Vueling, and Air Europa all have connecting flights to La Coruña Airport (Also known as Culleredo Airport) from Madrid, Spain as well as Barcelona, Spain.  TAP has connecting flights from Lisbon or O Porto, Portugal to La Coruña Airport as well.  TAP flies out of Newark Airport.  Iberia is the airline of Spain and will have the simplest travel options though not always the cheapest (They also own American Airlines and British Airways).  Look to buy your tickets early and on a weekday (prices can fluctuate from $550 dollars round trip to $1300).  Another local airport option is Santiago de Compostela Airport, though this is about an hour outside the city.</p>
          <p>Flights to Spain from New York City are overnight.  If you would like to arrive on Thursday you would leave Wednesday.  Flights usually depart from JFK between 5pm and 10pm.  You can plan your arrival for Friday however due to the time difference jet lag will take its toll on you that night.</p>
          <p>If more than 10 people plan to be traveling on the same flight you can contact the airline prior to booking to inquire about group travel rates.</p>
        </div>
