      <div class="panel panel-default">
        <div class="panel-heading panel-custom-green">
          Airports
        </div>
        <div class="panel-body">
          <p><a href="http://www.aena.es/en/a-coruna-airport/index.html"><b>La Coruna Airport (LCG)</b></a></p>
          <p>The airport closest to the city and to our wedding site.  This airport, sometimes known as Culleredo Airport due to the area it is in, only has domestic flights.  It is extremely small and mainly served by Iberia, Vueling, TAP and Air Europa.  There is a bus every 30-60 minutes from La Coruña airport to the area of Plaza Maria Pita/Puerta Real (ASC Línea 4051, A Coruña (Hospital Abente y Lago) – Vilaboa – Aeropuerto).</p>
          <p>The schedule can be found <a href="http://autoscalpita.com/tarifas-horarios/asc-linea-4051-coruna-puerta-real-vilaboa-aeropuerto/">here</a>.</p>
          <p>There are also taxis available at the airport. Car rental services can also be found, including Enterprise and Avis.</p>
          <br>
          <p><a href="http://www.aena.es/en/santiago-airport/index.html"><b>Santiago de Compestela Airport (SCQ)</b></a></p>
          <p>Larger airport about an hour drive/train ride from La Coruña.  This airport is accessible by international and domestic flights though no longer has direct flights from the US.</p>
          <br>
          <p><a href="http://www.aena.es/en/madrid-barajas-airport/index.html"><b>Adolfo Suarez Madrid Barajas Airport (MAD)</b></a></p>
          <p>Madrid Airport is the main hub for connecting flights in Spain.  Be aware that when arriving at Madrid from some international airlines (such as Iberia) you will be disembarking at T4S, a satellite terminal.  Connecting domestic flights to La Coruna generally leave from T4.  There is a tram which takes you from one terminal to the next.  Once you account for the time it takes to walk down the very long terminal, go through customs and security and to the next terminal this change can take 45 minutes to an hour if you are moving at a good pace.  I recommend leaving ample time between flights as a precaution (minimum of an hour and 20 minutes I would say).</p>
        </div>
      </div>
      <div class="panel panel-default">
