          Train Stations
        </div>
        <div class="panel-body">
          <p><a href="http://www.spain.info/en_US/informacion-practica/transportes/estaciones-tren/coruna_a/estacion_de_a_coruna.html"><b>San Cristobal Station</b></a></p>
          <p>Located on the Avenida del Ferrocarril, this train station in La Coruna can be reached by bus or taxi.  Local trains operated by RENFE can take you to other areas of Galicia or connect you to trains to different parts of Spain and Europe.</p>
          <br>
          <p><a href="https://rail.cc/en/santiago-de-compostela/santiago-de-compostela-railway-station/l1760"><b>Santiago de Compostela Station</b></a></p>
          <p>Santiago de Compostela can provide train service to Madrid as well as other major cities of Spain and beyond.  At the moment it is a 5 hour train ride from Santiago to Madrid.  Currently the AVE (High speed train) is still under construction however will provide 3 hour trips from Santiago de Compostela to Madrid.  Tickets can be bought online from the USA using the <a href="https://www.raileurope.com/index.html">Rail Europe</a> website.</p>
        </div>
