        <div class="panel-body">
          <p><b>Urban Bus</b></p>
          <p>La Coruña has a public bus system though much of the old city is easily walkable. Urban public buses are red. For out of town travel there are long distance buses and a train station.</p>
          <br>
          <p><a href="http://www.spain.info/en_US/informacion-practica/transportes/estaciones-autobus/coruna_a/estacion_de_autobuses_de_a_coruna.html"><b>Long Distance Bus</b></a></p>
          <p>The long distance bus station is located at Calle Caballeros, 21, near the train station.  Tel.:+34 981184335.  Coach buses are available to various towns and cities around Galicia.  There is a bus from this station to my town of Carnoedo, generally once an hour until 9pm.  It is a 45 minute trip along a scenic Atlantic adjacent road.</p>
